For physics simulation, I use OPAL (http://opal.sourceforge.net/), an
abstraction layer on top of ODE.  I used their servo motor
implementation for controlling joints, and it takes either the desired
angle or desired angular velocity of the joint.  From a quick look at
their implementation, it seems like they convert desired angles to
desired velocities and utilize the angular motor facility of ODE.

Vinod

